#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:27
msgid "📋 Summary"
msgstr "📋 まとめ"

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:29
msgid ""
"The sample data contains a longitude and latitude point cloud, along with "
"sample winds provided in the form of three separate eastward (``U``), "
"northward (``V``), and upward (``W``) vector components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:33
msgid ""
"The vector components are measured relative to each spatial sample point in "
"the point cloud."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:36
msgid ""
"No connectivity is provided within the sample data, so each point is a "
"separate location in a field of scattered points, and each point has an "
"associated wind vector independent of the others. We use the "
":meth:`geovista.bridge.Transform.from_points` method, passing the winds with"
" the ``vectors`` keyword, along with the associated sample points to "
"generate a point cloud mesh with attached vectors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:43
msgid ""
"The wind arrows are generated from this point cloud mesh via the "
":meth:`pyvista.DataSetFilters.glyph` method, which scales each arrow in size"
" and colour relative to the magnitude of its associated wind vector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:47
msgid ""
"Note that, we use all 3 wind components and amplify the upward (``W``) "
"vector component by a considerable factor for illustrative purposes. "
"Vertical winds are generally much smaller in magnitude, and tend not to be "
"very visible otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_uvw.rst:59
